                        </extent>
                        
                        
                        
                        <foliation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>251 folios (+ 2 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </foliation>
                        
                        
                        
                        <collation>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>25 quires of 10 leaves each (folios 4-241), 1 quire of 6 leaves (folios 242-248), marked by catchwords and signature at the end and with signature at the beginning.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </collation>
                        
                        
                        
                        <condition>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Damaged leaves at ends, repaired and infilled.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Usage stains.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Very dark paper.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </condition>
                     
                     
                     
                     </supportDesc>
                     
                     
                     
                     <layoutDesc>
                        
                        
                        
                        <layout columns="1 " ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Uniform layout. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Titles and inital words in larger characters.  </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Catchwords from folio to folio. </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Marginal notes and additions throughout, in a different hand than the main text.  </p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>Headings, subscriptions and opening wordshighlighted  in red and green ink.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </layout>
                     
                     
                     
                     </layoutDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  </objectDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <handDesc hands="1">
                     
                     
                     
                     <summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 15th century.</summary>
                     
                     
                     
                     <handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  </handDesc>
                  
                  
                  
                  <additions>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folios 1 and 251: two astronomical tables, probably a 16th century addition. Folios 1 is mutilated. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folios 2 and 3: an index to the biblical passages in the Dal᾿alat Al-Ha᾿irin, apparently of 17th century. The beginning is missing and in the last column (folio 3v) the biblical indications have not been filled. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folio 248: a short additional piece, of probably 16th century.</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     <p>Folios 249 and 250: fragments of Saadia Gaon's Arabic commentary on the Psalms; parchment leaves of probably 14th century. </p>
                  
                  
                  
                  </additions>
                  
                  
                  
